  "source": "_methodology/level3and3Ccontentdiscipline.md — the Level-3 & §3C content discipline (R1–R5)",
  "_doc": "The Level-3 lint (a 4th verifier beside validate/coverage) enforces the operating test on the authored content layers — Level 3 §4 propositions and §3C entries (and the FOR_MODEL prose fields compiled from them): a Level-3 block must contain ONLY payload Q&A pairs; flag every line that isn't one. It scans BOTH questions and answers, including the same-line '**Q:** … **A:** …' format. Rules: link_markers = cross_ref / inter-proposition-link lines that don't belong in §4 payload (relocate to the figure/links layer); meta_questions = analytical questions about form/structure/style rather than payload; forbidden_vocabulary = grammatical/linguistic jargon (WHOLE-WORD in prose only, not controlled slot-names); interpretive_labels; conditioning_qa = steering questions (Register?/Self-form?/…); compound = non-atomic answers (';'/','/' and ') with an entity-list guard so a single answer naming several entities is NOT flagged. It SURFACES drift; the human judges. tier 1 = unambiguous; tier 2 = judge-in-context.",
  "_slot_name_doc": "SC-0070: the forbidden-slot-NAME guard. An event_specific_slots KEY name must not carry grammatical/thematic-role vocabulary (the WEIRD/case-grammar priming the method avoids — CLAUDE.md:176 'event-participant slot names (giver/blesser/deceased/…), NEVER agent/patient/theme'). A key leaks iff an underscore-delimited TOKEN is in forbidden_slot_name_tokens; slot_name_allow exempts the fundamental communicative-event roles (Marcia's keep). Scoped to event_specific_slots keys ONLY — never the sanctioned L2 objects_in_scene / object_id physical-object namespace. tier 1 = BLOCK.",
  "forbidden_slot_name_tokens": ["agent", "recipient", "beneficiary", "subject", "object", "source", "locus", "owner", "argument", "antecedent", "referent"],
  "slot_name_allow": ["speaker", "addressee", "addressees"],
